Building reliable, observable AI systems requires more than prompt engineering — it demands rigorous engineering discipline that most agentic AI teams are still figuring out. That's exactly what I bring to the Agentic AI Engineer role at Benchling.

My current IBM Generative AI Engineering certification and AI Engineer Bootcamp training have given me hands-on experience with LLM workflows and agentic architectures. Critically, my 24-year performance engineering background maps directly onto LLM observability challenges: monitoring model inference latency and throughput against SLA thresholds is precisely what I did scaling systems to 12,000+ transactions per minute at Sprint and achieving sub-5-second transaction compliance at the USDA. The observability stack I've operated — Splunk, Prometheus, Grafana, AppDynamics — translates naturally to LLM evaluation tooling like LangSmith and Arize.

I'm available immediately, fully remote-ready, and bring a combination of proven observability expertise and active AI engineering training that most candidates in this space simply don't have. I'd welcome the conversation.

